37typedef struct
38{
39 char p_class[4];
40 char p_fourcc[4];
41 char psz_description[56];
42} staticentry_t;
43
44typedef struct
45{
46 char p_class[4];
47 char p_fourcc[4];
48 const char *psz_description;
49} entry_t;
50
51#define NULL4 "\x00\x00\x00\x00"
52
53/* XXX You don't want to see the preprocessor generated code ;) */
54#ifdef WORDS_BIGENDIAN
55# define FCC2STR(f) { ((f)>>24)&0xff, ((f)>>16)&0xff, ((f)>>8)&0xff, ((f)>>0)&0xff }
56#else
57# define FCC2STR(f) { ((f)>>0)&0xff, ((f)>>8)&0xff, ((f)>>16)&0xff, ((f)>>24)&0xff }
58#endif
59/* Begin a new class */
60#define B(a, c) { .p_class = FCC2STR(a), .p_fourcc = FCC2STR(a), .psz_description = c }
61/* Create a sub-class entry with description */
62#define E(b, c) { .p_class = NULL4, .p_fourcc = b, .psz_description = c }
63/* Create a sub-class entry without description (alias) */
64#define A(b) E(b, NULL4)

1515/* Create a fourcc from a string.
1516 * XXX it assumes that the string is at least four bytes */
1517static inline vlc_fourcc_t CreateFourcc( const char *psz_fourcc )
1518{
1519 return VLC_FOURCC( psz_fourcc[0], psz_fourcc[1],
1520 psz_fourcc[2], psz_fourcc[3] );
1521}
1522
1523/* */
1524static entry_t Lookup( const staticentry_t p_list[], vlc_fourcc_t i_fourcc )
1525{
1526 const char *p_class = NULL;
1527 const char *psz_description = NULL;
1528
1529 entry_t e = B(0, "");
1530
1531 for( int i = 0; ; i++ )
1532 {
1533 const staticentry_t *p = &p_list[i];
1534 const vlc_fourcc_t i_entry_fourcc = CreateFourcc( p->p_fourcc );
1535 const vlc_fourcc_t i_entry_class = CreateFourcc( p->p_class );
1536
1537 if( i_entry_fourcc == 0 )
1538 break;
1539
1540 if( i_entry_class != 0 )
1541 {
1542 p_class = p->p_class;
1543 psz_description = p->psz_description;
1544 }
1545
1546 if( i_entry_fourcc == i_fourcc )
1547 {
1548 assert( p_class != NULL );
1549
1550 memcpy( e.p_class, p_class, 4 );
1551 memcpy( e.p_fourcc, p->p_fourcc, 4 );
1552 e.psz_description = p->psz_description[0] != '\0' ?
1553 p->psz_description : psz_description;
1554 break;
1555 }
1556 }
1557 return e;
1558}
1559
1560/* */
1561static entry_t Find( int i_cat, vlc_fourcc_t i_fourcc )
1562{
1563 entry_t e;
1564
1565 switch( i_cat )
1566 {
1567 case VIDEO_ES:
1568 return Lookup( p_list_video, i_fourcc );
1569 case AUDIO_ES:
1570 return Lookup( p_list_audio, i_fourcc );
1571 case SPU_ES:
1572 return Lookup( p_list_spu, i_fourcc );
1573
1574 default:
1575 e = Find( VIDEO_ES, i_fourcc );
1576 if( CreateFourcc( e.p_class ) == 0 )
1577 e = Find( AUDIO_ES, i_fourcc );
1578 if( CreateFourcc( e.p_class ) == 0 )
1579 e = Find( SPU_ES, i_fourcc );
1580 return e;
1581 }
1582}
1583
1584/* */
1585vlc_fourcc_t vlc_fourcc_GetCodec( int i_cat, vlc_fourcc_t i_fourcc )
1586{
1587 entry_t e = Find( i_cat, i_fourcc );
1588
1589 if( CreateFourcc( e.p_class ) == 0 )
1590 return i_fourcc;
1591 return CreateFourcc( e.p_class );
1592}
1593
1594vlc_fourcc_t vlc_fourcc_GetCodecFromString( int i_cat, const char *psz_fourcc )
1595{
1596 if( !psz_fourcc || strlen(psz_fourcc) != 4 )
1597 return 0;
1598 return vlc_fourcc_GetCodec( i_cat,
1599 VLC_FOURCC( psz_fourcc[0], psz_fourcc[1],
1600 psz_fourcc[2], psz_fourcc[3] ) );
1601}
1602
1603vlc_fourcc_t vlc_fourcc_GetCodecAudio( vlc_fourcc_t i_fourcc, int i_bits )
1604{
1605 const int i_bytes = ( i_bits + 7 ) / 8;
1606
1607 if( i_fourcc == VLC_FOURCC( 'a', 'f', 'l', 't' ) )
1608 {
1609 switch( i_bytes )
1610 {
1611 case 4:
1612 return VLC_CODEC_FL32;
1613 case 8:
1614 return VLC_CODEC_FL64;
1615 default:
1616 return 0;
1617 }
1618 }
1619 else if( i_fourcc == VLC_FOURCC( 'a', 'r', 'a', 'w' ) )
1620 {
1621 switch( i_bytes )
1622 {
1623 case 1:
1624 return VLC_CODEC_U8;
1625 case 2:
1626 return VLC_CODEC_S16L;
1627 case 3:
1628 return VLC_CODEC_S24L;
1629 break;
1630 case 4:
1631 return VLC_CODEC_S32L;
1632 default:
1633 return 0;
1634 }
1635 }
1636 else if( i_fourcc == VLC_FOURCC( 't', 'w', 'o', 's' ) )
1637 {
1638 switch( i_bytes )
1639 {
1640 case 1:
1641 return VLC_CODEC_S8;
1642 case 2:
1643 return VLC_CODEC_S16B;
1644 case 3:
1645 return VLC_CODEC_S24B;
1646 case 4:
1647 return VLC_CODEC_S32B;
1648 default:
1649 return 0;
1650 }
1651 }
1652 else if( i_fourcc == VLC_FOURCC( 's', 'o', 'w', 't' ) )
1653 {
1654 switch( i_bytes )
1655 {
1656 case 1:
1657 return VLC_CODEC_S8;
1658 case 2:
1659 return VLC_CODEC_S16L;
1660 case 3:
1661 return VLC_CODEC_S24L;
1662 case 4:
1663 return VLC_CODEC_S32L;
1664 default:
1665 return 0;
1666 }
1667 }
1668 else
1669 {
1670 return vlc_fourcc_GetCodec( AUDIO_ES, i_fourcc );
1671 }
1672}
1673
1674/* */
1675const char *vlc_fourcc_GetDescription( int i_cat, vlc_fourcc_t i_fourcc )
1676{
1677 entry_t e = Find( i_cat, i_fourcc );
1678
1679 return e.psz_description;
1680}

1963 const vlc_fourcc_t *pp_fallback[],
1964 const vlc_fourcc_t p_list[] )
1965{

1970 }
1971 return p_list;

1983bool vlc_fourcc_AreUVPlanesSwapped( vlc_fourcc_t a, vlc_fourcc_t b )
1984{
1985 static const vlc_fourcc_t pp_swapped[][4] = {
1986 { VLC_CODEC_YV12, VLC_CODEC_I420, VLC_CODEC_J420, 0 },
1987 { VLC_CODEC_YV9, VLC_CODEC_I410, 0 },
1988 { 0 }
1989 };
1990
1991 for( int i = 0; pp_swapped[i][0]; i++ )
1992 {
1993 if( pp_swapped[i][0] == b )
1994 {
1995 vlc_fourcc_t t = a;
1996 a = b;
1997 b = t;
1998 }
1999 if( pp_swapped[i][0] != a )
2000 continue;
2001 for( int j = 1; pp_swapped[i][j]; j++ )
2002 {
2003 if( pp_swapped[i][j] == b )
2004 return true;
2005 }
2006 }
2007 return false;
2008}

2108const vlc_chroma_description_t *vlc_fourcc_GetChromaDescription( vlc_fourcc_t i_fourcc )
2109{
2110 for( unsigned i = 0; p_list_chroma_description[i].p_fourcc[0]; i++ )
2111 {
2112 const vlc_fourcc_t *p_fourcc = p_list_chroma_description[i].p_fourcc;
2113 for( unsigned j = 0; j < 4 && p_fourcc[j] != 0; j++ )
2114 {
2115 if( p_fourcc[j] == i_fourcc )
2116 return &p_list_chroma_description[i].description;
2117 }
2118 }
2119 return NULL;
2120}
